commit_message: Downgrade xnio to allow building native image (due to https://github.com/SoftInstigate/graalvm-undertow-issue)
Fix log error message on plugin registration error
remove downgraded xnio dependency from commons
Update native-image build configuration + remove 'plugins' in security packages + upgrade xnio
Fix mongoPermissionWhitelistMgmtRequests (not allowing creating attachments) + refactor package of security plugins
Refactor how PipelineInfo is obtained from request
Fix operationResult not availabe in PATCH document response
Interceptors can be implemented in JavaScript on GraalVM
Remove unused imports + some minor refactoring

The ACL permission properties overriddenProps, readFilter and writeFilter can use variables @now, @user, @user._id, ecc + all mongo related security interceptors moved to package security/src/main/java/org/restheart/security/plugins/interceptors/mongo
Remove debug message from test node service nodeModulePromise.js
MongoPermissionsProtectedProps handles dot notation on update operators
Log 'Connecting to MongoDB...' before starting connection attempt
Script to generate keystore now creates a Certificate Authority to issue the certificate, this allows the certificate to be imported and used by modern browsers
Update configuration file removing option to used embedded keystore
Remove embedded keystore with self singed certificate
Add support for mongo.overriddenProps ACL permission to force properties to predefined values
Add support for mongo.protectedProps ACL permission to protect properties to be written
Default values for ACL permission mongo.whitelist* and mongo.allowAllWriteModes is false
Add support for mongo.hiddenProps ACL permission to hide properties from the response

MongoDB bulk delete, bulk patch and db management operations are forbidden unless the applied ACL permission explicitly whitelists them. Write mode is forced to have POST only inserting, PUT and PATCH only updating unless the applied ACL permission explicitly allows using the ?wm query parameter
fileAclAuthorizer supports same extended permission options than mongoAclAuthorizer
Add script to generate the java keystore from letsencrypt certificate archive
Improve performance of NodeService by caching javascript code evaluation
Allow node plugins to return Promise + handle timeout
Allow RESTHeart to be run on GraalVM with node --jvm and add NodeService to deploy node plugins
PolyglotDeployer only activates when running on GraalVM
JavaScript services can be bound to any uri and secured via options
Services can be plugged programmatically with PluginsRegistry.plugService()
JavaScript plugins have access to the MongoClient if initialized by MongoService
Refactoring of PolyglotDeployer + update native-image configuration
Add prototype restheart-polyglot module that allows implementing plugins in JavaScript on GraalVM
Enhance ChannelReader by using ByteBufferPool from Exchange

Add simplifiedSecurityWriteMode that restricts the write requests to allow POST to only insert new documents and PUT and PATCH to only update existing documents; this greatly simplifies the definition of security permissions
Replate upsert query paramter with writeMode that allows to specify INSERT, UPDATE and UPSERT write modes
Start support for update-only write requests via query parameter ?upsert=false

Describe license and support options [skip ci]

Fix error setting final field identityManager via reflection

Add request and response generic parameters to Service interface. Use this information to instantiate the correct request and response objects for the handling service. ResponseSender sends the content stored in the response object used by the handling Service

Modified the db cursor pre-allocation engine so that cursors in the pool won't be used if REQUESTED_SKIPS - POOL_SKIPS > 10% * REQUESTED_SKIPS. The cursor from the pool need to be iterated via the next() method (REQUESTED_SKIPS - POOL_SKIPS) times to reach the requested page; since skip() is more efficient than next(), using the cursor in the pool is worthwhile only if next() has to be used less than 10% * REQUESTED_SKIPS times.
small change with huge performance improvement! yeahhhhh
